The paper deals with problems related to clusterization and cut problems, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The paper also establishes a new connection between these two classes of problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
